A MAN has died after a car plunged down an embankment.
Police found his body inside a silver Hyundai near the A71 between Allanton and Morningside in Wishaw, Lanarkshire.
The man, who has not been named, was discovered shortly before 1pm today.
A force spokeswoman said: “Inquiries are ongoing to establish the cause.”
Roads between Allanton and Morningside are closed while officers carry out investigations and local diversions are in place.
Anyone with information about the incident is asked to contact Police Scotland on the non-emergency 101 number.
